# --- ICM reference clone (already tracked upstream) ---
_templates/icm-reference/

# --- Personal notes inside the bundled Free Edition skill ---
# The skill copy we bundle is generic. The session note from one specific
# user's run is personal and should not ship with the public template.
**/edu-lake-br-session-*.md

# --- Active workspaces (post-setup) ---
# Templates in _templates/ ARE tracked (they're the reusable scaffolding).
# The ibge-sidra-population-pipeline/ workspace IS tracked as the
# end-to-end worked example (proof the template works).
# Other active workspaces under ~/workspaces/<name>-pipeline/ are
# personal projects and should NOT be committed here. Initialize a
# separate repo inside the active workspace if you want to version it.
# Add new active workspaces to the ignore list as you create them:
# kaggle-credit-pipeline/
# brasil-io-eleicoes-pipeline/

# --- Standard ignores ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# --- Databricks / Python noise ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
*.egg-info/

# --- Databricks notebook cell output (when running locally) ---
.databricks/
*.dbc

# --- Secrets (never commit tokens, even if Free Edition) ---
.env
.env.local
*.pem
*.key
databrickscfg